  "prompt": "Who all can apply the title \"Er.\" as a prefix for their names?",
  "response": "The title \"Er.\" is commonly used as a prefix for individuals who have completed a degree in engineering. It stands for \"Engineer\" and is typically used in countries like India and Pakistan, where it is recognized as a professional title for qualified engineers. \n\nTo use the title \"Er.\", individuals generally need to have completed a Bachelor's degree in Engineering (B.E. or B.Tech) or a higher degree in the field. It is often used by civil, mechanical, electrical, computer, and other branches of engineering graduates.\n\nIn summary, anyone who has a valid engineering degree and is recognized as an engineer in their respective country or profession can apply the title \"Er.\" before their name.",
